			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>An Extensive Catalog of Operators for the Coupled Evolution of Metamodels and Models</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MarkusHerrmannsdörfer.html">Markus Herrmannsdörfer</a>, <a href="../profile/SanderDVermolen.html">Sander D. Vermolen</a>, <a href="../profile/GuidoWachsmuth.html">Guido Wachsmuth</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_10">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_10</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagM">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> It provides a catalog of operators specifically for coupled evolution scenarios (metamodel + model co-adaptation).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The operators essentially define systematic transformation steps for migration/co-evolution.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> The catalog organizes and characterizes change operators as a basis for analyzing and managing evolution.
</li></ul></li></ul>
